# === Environment & Secrets ===
.env
.env.*
.env.local
.env.production
js/env.js
*.pem
*.key
*.cert

# === Per-deployment server config ===
# Written by GPUCONFIGURE.bat → gpu-configure.html admin UI.
# Each operator picks their own resource tier; host-specific.
server/resource-config.json

# === T18.12 per-machine runtime artifact ===
# autoClearStaleState() writes SHA256 of the brain-logic source files
# to this file on every boot. Compared against the prior-boot value to
# decide whether to preserve or clear state. Per-machine + per-boot
# runtime data; must not be committed. Each clone computes its own
# hash on first boot.
server/brain-code-hash.json

# === T18.37 per-machine runtime log ===
# start.bat + Savestart.bat redirect node brain-server.js stdout/stderr
# to server/server.log so operators can tail heartbeat + brain info even
# if the launcher terminal goes invisible (Windows Terminal rendering
# glitches). Per-boot runtime data; must not be committed.
server/server.log

# === 114.19es.5 dictionary disk cache ===
# definition-service.js writes K-VOCAB definitions fetched from
# dictionaryapi.dev to this file every 5 min during runs and on graceful
# shutdown. Per-machine runtime cache (grows up to ~10k entries / few MB);
# rebuilds organically on cache miss + API fetch. Not load-bearing, not
# committable.
server/definition-cache.json
server/boot-error.log

# === Claude Code — Layer 0 .claude/ IP boundary ===
# Lab workflow internals (personas, agents, skills, ImHanddicapped.txt,
# session state, command bodies) stay LOCAL — never committed, never
# deployed. Blanket-ignore the whole tree so no `git add -A` can ever
# sweep the persona/workflow IP into a push (especially before a public
# pre-alpha deploy). A few legacy files (CLAUDE.md / CONSTRAINTS.md /
# statusline.sh) were tracked before this guard landed; whether to
# `git rm --cached` them is a separate explicit decision.
.claude/

# === Workflow docs — tracked for project documentation ===
# (Previously ignored as "generated at runtime" but these are real docs now)

# === Archived docs — local-only history, not tracked ===
# Phase 13 pre-refactor audits (KILL_LIST, VESTIGIAL, SEMANTIC_GAP) +
# stale session snapshots (NOW.md) moved here when the work they
# tracked got absorbed into FINALIZED.md. Kept on disk so Gee can
# grep the history locally, but not pushed.
docs/archive/

# === Pollinations output ===
pollinations-output/

